title: Intro
lyrics:
It felt like birth
We had a careful, meticulous hopeful love, that led to a hard labor Ignited by heartbreak
It felt like birth the way I cried
In the cold I felt naked and exposed
Awake, alone
Confused, uncomfortable and incapable of simply breathing

Painful and beautiful at the same time

And when I grew, when I found myself

I learned I existed still

I realized that after all...

There is life after love
